This paper is about cross-lingual word embeddings, which is a topic related to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also proposes an unsupervised method for aligning monolingual word embeddings, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for learning the embeddings, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on low-resource language pairs, which may involve techniques from neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions experiments on image captioning, which may involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
